## KNN: no training, all inference

```python
def knn_predict(X_train, y_train, x, k):
    dists = sorted(
        (sum((a - b) ** 2 for a, b in zip(pt, x)), lbl)
        for pt, lbl in zip(X_train, y_train)
    )
    top = dists[:min(k, len(dists))]   # k > n: use all points
    votes = Counter(lbl for _, lbl in top)
    best = max(votes.values())
    tied = {lbl for lbl, c in votes.items() if c == best}
    for _, lbl in top:                 # nearest tied class wins
        if lbl in tied:
            return lbl
```

Three decisions worth narrating: squared distance (no sqrt), k > n fallback, and an explicit tie rule.
